# Deterministic line endings for cross-platform byte-identity test gates.
#
# Windows CI runners default to core.autocrlf=true. Without this file the
# committed-LF text fixtures get checked out with CRLF on Windows, which
# breaks SHA256 / byte-identity assertions:
#   - tests/main/repack.loose-parity.spec.ts  (SIMPLE_TEST.atlas baseline)
#   - tests/fixtures/repack-baselines.json     (hash baselines)
#   - fixtures/SLIDER_4_3/NOTES.txt            (slider triangulation)
# Scoped to the fixture/baseline text types on purpose (no repo-wide
# `* text=auto`) so this never triggers a surprise mass renormalization.
# Image assets are marked binary so they are never EOL/encoding-normalized
# (protects the PNG SHA256 baselines).

*.atlas  text eol=lf
*.json   text eol=lf
*.txt    text eol=lf

*.png    binary
*.jpg    binary
*.jpeg   binary
*.webp   binary
